  artworkTitle: "The East Offering Its Riches to Britannia",
  artworkCredit: "Spiridione Roma, 1778",
  artworkCaption:
    "Roma's allegory of Eastern submission to Britain — the imperial confidence that emboldened evangelicals like Grant to demand the Company serve as an instrument of Christian redemption.",
  map: "/images/slide_213_img_1.png",
