  body: "The myths the Nazis drew upon were Christian myths. 'Let his blood be on us and on our children' — the charge that Jews had accepted responsibility for Christ's death had seen them condemned as agents of the Devil across centuries. In Slovakia, the puppet regime was headed by a priest. In Croatia, over thirty thousand Jews were murdered. Yet there were also Christians who risked everything: Bonhoeffer conspired against Hitler and was hanged; priests in Hungary 'frantically issued baptismal certificates, knowing that they might be shot for doing so.' Pius XII lamented privately: 'They deplore the fact that the Pope does not speak. But the pope cannot speak. If he spoke, things would be worse.' Five hundred Jews were given shelter in the pope's summer residence. Among the SS, 'the pope was derided as a rabbi.'",
