  body: "Angela Merkel, speaking to teenagers in a Rostock school gymnasium, was confronted by Reem Sahwil, a Palestinian girl facing deportation. Merkel explained awkwardly: 'You know that in the Palestinian refugee camps in Lebanon there are thousands and thousands, and if we were to say you can all come — we just couldn't manage.' When Sahwil began to cry, Merkel stroked her hair: 'I know it's difficult for you.' Yet within weeks, Merkel reversed course. Thousands upon thousands of migrants were pouring through the Balkans. In Hungary, Victor Orban warned that 'Europe's soul was at stake.' Merkel refused to close Germany's borders. Football fans raised banners of welcome. She declared that the scenes 'painted a picture of Germany which can make us proud of our country.'",
