  body: "Harvey Weinstein held court in a suite at the Peninsula Beverly Hills, where housekeepers earning $9.51 an hour cleaned up after guests paying over two thousand dollars a night. Between a movie tycoon and the woman tidying his towels there was 'an almost vertiginous imbalance of power.' Across America, one in four women experienced workplace sexual harassment. Bernard of Clairvaux had lamented: 'To be always with a woman and not to have sexual relations with her is more difficult than to raise the dead.' Two thousand years of Christian sexual morality had struggled to tame the very appetites that Hollywood celebrated. Pulp Fiction had turned amorality into box-office gold. 'Sexual repression was boring — and to be boring was box-office death.'",
